    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Call to Curb The Cost of Electricity</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Sergio Brasesco letter questions why New York State legislature is not doing anything to curb runaway electric and gas costs (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I felt compelled to write you after reading with much interest the ongoing debate over our astronomical electric and gas costs.</p>
        <p>After opening my Con Edison bill, once again, over $2,500 just for electric this summer! I realize that something must be done within the Legislature to curb these runaway costs. With summer halfway over and temperatures being moderate, I find it hard to believe that costs are so high. Con Edison offers many excuses, but no solutions.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I felt compelled to write you after reading with much interest the ongoing debate over our astronomical electric and gas costs.</p>
        <p>After opening my Con Edison bill, once again, over $2,500 just for electric this summer! I realize that something must be done within the Legislature to curb these runaway costs. With summer halfway over and temperatures being moderate, I find it hard to believe that costs are so high. Con Edison offers many excuses, but no solutions.</p>
        <p>As a small business owner my electric and gas bills will soon be higher than my rent! What have things come to?</p>
        <p>SERGIO BRASESCO  Rye Brook</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
